  "format": "Sean Fennessey pulls in Rob Harvilla and Bandsplain's Yasi Salek to take two of 2024's most-watched non-movies seriously: Netflix's snowman rom-com 'Hot Frosty' and Disney's 'Moana 2.' Then Sean sits down with Garrett Price about the 'Yacht Rock' documentary.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "‘Hot Frosty’",
      "note": "Sean Fennessey, Rob Harvilla, Yasi Salek",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Hot Frosty",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Netflix's snowman rom-com: a young widow (Lacey Chabert) builds a snowman who comes to life as a himbo (Dustin Milligan, the Schitt's Creek vet), with Craig Robinson as a sheriff who seems to be in a different movie than everyone else. Rob wanted the widow to sleep with the snowman and felt cheated when she didn't; Yasi, a devoted watcher of the streaming-Christmas genre, rates it an 11 out of 10. Licenses Pretty Woman for a shopping montage and closes on a fake-Coldplay needle drop."
        },
        {
          "title": "Mean Girls (2004)",
          "year": 2004,
          "note": "Lacey Chabert's high point; Hot Frosty winks at it when Lindsay Lohan shows up on a TV in the background."
        },
        {
          "title": "Mean Girls",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "The musical remake, which Sean takes as evidence that Mean Girls is somehow back in the culture."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Crow (1994)",
          "year": 1994,
          "note": "The reason Yasi is on the show: Sean had planned a whole episode around her love of the original."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Crow",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "The Bill Skarsgård reimagining, which stunk so thoroughly Sean gave it four minutes on air and no episode of its own."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "‘Moana 2’",
